# VidyaFund AI вЂ” Implementation Plan

An institutional student-funding routing platform that prevents dependency by enforcing minimum thresholds, fixed categories, frequency caps, and institutional-only funding.

## Architecture Overview

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph Frontend ["React + Tailwind Frontend"]
        SR[Student Request Form]
        FD[Funder Dashboard]
        ST[Status Tracker]
    end

    subgraph Backend ["FastAPI Backend"]
        AUTH[JWT Auth Middleware]
        API[API Routes]
        VA[Verification Agent]
        UE[Urgency Engine]
        ME[Matching Engine]
        IA[Impact Agent]
        RP[Razorpay Service]
    end

    subgraph Database ["PostgreSQL"]
        DB[(Tables: users, students,<br/>requests, funders, matches,<br/>transactions, impact_logs)]
    end

    SR --> AUTH --> API
    FD --> AUTH
    ST --> AUTH
    API --> VA
    API --> UE
    API --> ME
    API --> IA
    API --> RP
    API --> DB
```

## Core Rules Enforcement Summary

| Rule | Where Enforced | How |
|------|---------------|-----|
| **Rs. 2,000 minimum** | DB `CHECK` constraint + API validation + Frontend inline validation | `amount >= 2000` at all 3 layers |
| **Fixed categories** | DB `ENUM` type + API Pydantic enum + Frontend fixed dropdown | `exam_fee`, `certification_fee`, `device_repair`, `interview_travel` |
| **1-2 requests/year** | DB query check + API pre-insert validation | Count existing requests for `student_id` in current academic year |
| **Institutional only** | DB `funder_type` enum + No individual donor UI/API | CSR, alumni association, college welfare office only |

