## Phase 1: Database Schema (PostgreSQL)

### Tables

#### `users`
| Column | Type | Constraints |
|--------|------|-------------|
| id | UUID | PK, DEFAULT gen_random_uuid() |
| email | VARCHAR(255) | UNIQUE, NOT NULL |
| password_hash | VARCHAR(255) | NOT NULL |
| full_name | VARCHAR(255) | NOT NULL |
| role | ENUM('student','funder','admin') | NOT NULL |
| created_at | TIMESTAMP | DEFAULT NOW() |

#### `students`
| Column | Type | Constraints |
|--------|------|-------------|
| id | UUID | PK, DEFAULT gen_random_uuid() |
| user_id | UUID | FK в†’ users.id, UNIQUE |
| institution | VARCHAR(255) | NOT NULL |
| enrollment_id | VARCHAR(100) | UNIQUE, NOT NULL |
| academic_year | VARCHAR(10) | NOT NULL (e.g. '2025-26') |
| request_count | INTEGER | DEFAULT 0, CHECK >= 0 |

#### `requests`
| Column | Type | Constraints |
|--------|------|-------------|
| id | UUID | PK |
| student_id | UUID | FK в†’ students.id |
| category | ENUM('exam_fee','certification_fee','device_repair','interview_travel') | NOT NULL |
| amount | INTEGER | NOT NULL, **CHECK (amount >= 2000)** |
| description | TEXT | NOT NULL |
| deadline_date | DATE | NOT NULL |
| document_url | VARCHAR(500) | |
| verification_score | INTEGER | DEFAULT NULL |
| verification_flags | JSONB | DEFAULT '[]' |
| urgency_level | VARCHAR(10) | DEFAULT NULL |
| review_flag | BOOLEAN | DEFAULT FALSE |
| status | ENUM('submitted','verified','matched','approved','disbursed','completed','rejected') | DEFAULT 'submitted' |
| academic_year | VARCHAR(10) | NOT NULL |
| created_at | TIMESTAMP | DEFAULT NOW() |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The `CHECK (amount >= 2000)` constraint is the database-level enforcement of Core Rule 1. Even if the API/frontend validation is bypassed, the DB will reject sub-Rs.2000 inserts.

#### `funders`
| Column | Type | Constraints |
|--------|------|-------------|
| id | UUID | PK |
| user_id | UUID | FK в†’ users.id, UNIQUE |
| org_name | VARCHAR(255) | NOT NULL |
| funder_type | ENUM('csr_program','alumni_association','college_welfare') | NOT NULL |
| categories_supported | JSONB | NOT NULL (array of supported categories) |
| available_balance | INTEGER | DEFAULT 0 |
| avg_payout_days | FLOAT | DEFAULT 3.0 |

#### `matches`
| Column | Type | Constraints |
|--------|------|-------------|
| id | UUID | PK |
| request_id | UUID | FK в†’ requests.id |
| funder_id | UUID | FK в†’ funders.id |
| match_score | FLOAT | NOT NULL |
| status | ENUM('proposed','accepted','rejected') | DEFAULT 'proposed' |
| created_at | TIMESTAMP | DEFAULT NOW() |

#### `transactions`
| Column | Type | Constraints |
|--------|------|-------------|
| id | UUID | PK |
| match_id | UUID | FK в†’ matches.id |
| razorpay_order_id | VARCHAR(255) | |
| razorpay_payment_id | VARCHAR(255) | |
| amount | INTEGER | NOT NULL |
| status | ENUM('pending','funded','failed') | DEFAULT 'pending' |
| created_at | TIMESTAMP | DEFAULT NOW() |

#### `impact_logs`
| Column | Type | Constraints |
|--------|------|-------------|
| id | UUID | PK |
| transaction_id | UUID | FK в†’ transactions.id |
| report_url | VARCHAR(500) | NOT NULL |
| funder_name | VARCHAR(255) | NOT NULL |
| amount | INTEGER | NOT NULL |
| category | VARCHAR(50) | NOT NULL |
| outcome | TEXT | |
| generated_at | TIMESTAMP | DEFAULT NOW() |

### Implementation Notes
- Use SQLAlchemy 2.0 `Mapped`/`mapped_column` syntax with async engine via `asyncpg`
- For hackathon speed, use `Base.metadata.create_all()` for initial setup (skip Alembic migrations)
- Enums defined as Python `enum.Enum` mapped to PostgreSQL ENUM types

