## Phase 3: Verification Agent

```python
# Pseudocode for verification_agent.py
async def verify_document(file_path: str) -> dict:
    # 1. OCR extraction
    if file_path.endswith('.pdf'):
        images = convert_from_path(file_path, dpi=300)
        text = "".join(pytesseract.image_to_string(img) for img in images)
    else:
        text = pytesseract.image_to_string(Image.open(file_path))
    
    # 2. GPT-4o-mini analysis
    prompt = f"""Analyze this document text for a student funding request.
    Score authenticity 0-100. Flag any fraud indicators.
    Document text: {text}
    Return JSON: {{"verification_score": int, "flags": [str]}}"""
    
    response = openai_client.chat.completions.create(
        model="gpt-4o-mini",
        messages=[{"role": "user", "content": prompt}],
        response_format={"type": "json_object"}
    )
    return json.loads(response.choices[0].message.content)
```

> [!NOTE]
> For the hackathon demo, if Tesseract is not installed on the machine, we'll provide a fallback mock that returns a plausible score (75-95) with empty flags. This ensures the demo flow works regardless of OCR setup.

